      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RISE FOR TINA (7) jumped from the middle and safely held on debut at this track over 515m (30.63). Likely to improve sharply this time. TRUNKEY MOTH (3) went straight to the front and never headed when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 6th and beaten 16 lengths at this track (30.53). Good beginner aided by a nice draw. One of the better hopes. TEQUILA GIRL (6) steps out for the first time at this circuit. Comes here a last start placegetter at Taree Super Track in a Grade 5 (17.79). Has good early speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Must be included in calculations. PAY ME (1) can measure up with the right run.",
